Variables:
Are like boxes/containers which can hold data for us.
We can change the data later on if we want.
We can reuse the dame variable as many times as we want.
There are 8 basic/primitive data types.
Four basic data types to store whole numbers.
For e.g. 1) byte, 2) short, 3) int, 4) long.
2 basic data types to store decimal numbers.
1) float, 2) double.
1 data type.
To store characters;
char
To store true/false;
boolean
NonPrimitive:
1)String
